messages.title: It's a two horse race here!
messages.content: Only hard-working Jo Shaw can beat Labour here. The Tories came a distant third place last time.

messages.title: Fighting for a Fairer Camden
messages.content: Jo Shaw and the Lib Dem Team - active on local issues, freezing council tax, saving local hospital services, safer community policing, against the war in Iraq.

messages.title: Putting Camden First
messages.content: Delivering Real Change for You - Local health campaigner Jo Shaw vows to keep local Accident & Emergency department open and freeze Council tax. Lib Dems have good track record of action in Camden.

keyPolicies.policyDescription: Jo Shaw and the Lib Dem Team are focused on keeping local hospital services open, fighting for a safer community, freezing council tax, and were against Labour's war in Iraq.

mentions.tacticalSituation: Jo Shaw is the only candidate that can beat Labour, as Conservatives can't win in Camden.

issues.economy: Lib Dems have frozen Council tax.
issues.health: Campaign to save local hospital services and keep the Whittington Hospital A&E open.

housing.content: Jo Shaw is fighting to save local hospital services.

leaflet.personalStatement: Jo Shaw is a hardworking campaigner, giving the constituency a strong voice.

images.caption: Images showing Jo Shaw actively engaging with the community and protesting against local hospital closures.
